.TH arctgz 7 "2026-07-19" "arctgz 0.1.0" "Miscellaneous Information Manual"
.SH NAME
arctgz \- safety-first project initialisation library for the arctgz archive format
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
\fBuse arctgz::{init, ArctgzConfig, ArctgzError};\fP
\fBuse std::path::Path;\fP

\fBfn init(project_path: &Path, force: bool) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP

\fBstruct ArctgzConfig {\fP
    \fBpub name:    String,\fP
    \fBpub version: String,\fP
    \fBpub include: Vec<String>,\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBimpl ArctgzConfig {\fP
    \fBpub fn validate(&self) -> Result<(), ArctgzError>;\fP
\fB}\fP

\fBenum ArctgzError { ... }\fP
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The arctgz library offers a single, robust \fBinit\fP() function that scaffolds a new arctgz project directory.
It enforces strict path confinement, validates all metadata before touching the filesystem, and creates the project configuration file atomically.
.PP
\fBinit\fP() will:
.IP \(bu 2
create the project root directory if it does not already exist,
.IP \(bu
write a default \fBarctgz.init\fP JSON configuration file,
.IP \(bu
create an empty \fBinclude/\fP sub-directory.
.PP
If the target directory already contains an \fBarctgz.init\fP file the operation fails immediately (even when \fBforce\fP is \fBtrue\fP), preventing accidental overwrites of an existing project.
.PP
All paths are resolved via \fBstd::fs::canonicalize\fP() (\fBrealpath\fP(3) semantics), so symbolic links are transparently followed during the home-directory confinement check.
The library is tested on Linux, macOS and Windows.
.SH INIT FUNCTION
.TP
\fBinit\fP(\fIproject_path\fP, \fIforce\fP)
.RS
.TP
\fIproject_path\fP
A reference to a \fBstd::path::Path\fP.
Must not be empty and must refer to a directory (or a non-existent location) that resides inside the user's home directory.
.TP
\fIforce\fP
If \fBtrue\fP, the function will proceed even when the target directory is not empty, provided no \fBarctgz.init\fP file already exists.
Existing files are never overwritten.
.PP
Returns \fBOk(())\fP on success, or an \fBArctgzError\fP on failure.
.RE
.SH TYPES
.TP
\fBArctgzConfig\fP
Represents the contents of the \fBarctgz.init\fP configuration file.
.RS
.PP
Fields:
.RS
.TP
\fBname\fP
project name (default \fB"untitled"\fP).
.TP
\fBversion\fP
semantic version (default \fB"0.1.0"\fP).
.TP
\fBinclude\fP
list of relative resource paths (default \fB[]\fP).
.RE
.PP
\fBvalidate\fP()
.br
Checks:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\fBname\fP is non-empty, \(<= 255 chars, and contains only alphanumerics, '\-' or '_',
.IP \(bu
\fBversion\fP is a valid semver string,
.IP \(bu
\fBinclude\fP paths are relative, do not contain "\fB..\fP", and the list has at most 100 entries.
.RE
.PP
Returns \fBOk(())\fP or an \fBArctgzError::ConfigValidation\fP.
.RE
.TP
\fBArctgzError\fP
An enumeration covering all failure cases:
.RS
.TP
\fBIo(std::io::Error)\fP
An I/O error occurred during directory creation or file writing.
.TP
\fBJson(serde_json::Error)\fP
JSON serialisation/deserialisation failure.
.TP
\fBAlreadyInitialized\fP
An \fBarctgz.init\fP file already exists in the target directory.
.TP
\fBInvalidPath(String)\fP
The supplied path is empty, or the path exists but is not a directory.
.TP
\fBPathNotAllowed(String)\fP
The canonicalised path lies outside the user's home directory.
.TP
\fBDirectoryNotEmpty(String)\fP
The directory exists, is not empty, and \fBforce\fP was \fBfalse\fP.
.TP
\fBConfigValidation(String)\fP
\fBArctgzConfig::validate\fP() failed with a human-readable message.
.RE
.SH ERRORS
The conditions that cause \fBinit\fP() to return each error variant are documented under \fBArctgzError\fP above.
Callers should pattern-match on the error variant to provide appropriate feedback.
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
\fBuse std::path::Path;\fP
\fBuse arctgz;\fP

\fBfn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {\fP
    \fB// scaffold a new project in ~/my-project\fP
    \fBlet project_path = Path::new("./my-project");\fP
    \fBarctgz::init(project_path, false)?;\fP
    \fBprintln!("Project created successfully");\fP
    \fBOk(())\fP
\fB}\fP
.fi
.PP
After a successful run the directory looks like:
.PP
.nf
\fBmy-project/\fP
\fB\(a`-- arctgz.init\fP
\fB\(a`-- include/\fP
.fi
.PP
The generated \fBarctgz.init\fP will contain:
.PP
.nf
\fB{\fP
  \fB"name": "untitled",\fP
  \fB"version": "0.1.0",\fP
  \fB"include": []\fP
\fB}\fP
.fi
.SH FILES
.TP
\fBarctgz.init\fP
JSON file holding project metadata.
Written atomically with \fBcreate_new(true)\fP \(en the file is never truncated or overwritten.
.TP
\fBinclude/\fP
An empty directory that serves as the default location for resource files that will be bundled into the final archive.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBHOME\fP
The library obtains the home directory via the \fBdirs\fP crate.
If \fBHOME\fP is not set it falls back to platform-specific methods.
If no home directory can be determined, \fBinit\fP() fails with a \fBPathNotAllowed\fP error for any relative path.
.SH SECURITY CONSIDERATIONS
.IP \(bu 2
Path confinement \(en only paths inside the user's home directory are permitted.
Symlink attacks are neutralised by canonicalisation before the check.
.IP \(bu
Atomic config creation \(en the configuration file is opened with \fBcreate_new(true)\fP, preventing TOCTOU races.
.IP \(bu
Input validation \(en project name, version and include paths are validated before any filesystem modification, reducing the risk of injection or malformed metadata.
.SH VERSION
arctgz 0.1.0 \(en early development release.
Only project initialisation is implemented.
Future releases will add compile, verify and extract functionality.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBsemver\fP(7),
\fBrealpath\fP(3),
\fBserde_json\fP(5),
\fBdirs\fP(7)
.SH BUGS
The library is in early development.
Report issues at the project repository.
.PP
The \fBinclude/\fP directory is always created empty; there is currently no mechanism to add files during initialisation.
This will be addressed in a future release.
